{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_38ca2149b6464620a14fa9f6","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"girepository-2.0 manylinux wheel pip install 2025\"\n\nThe user wants me to search for information about \"girepository-2.0 manylinux wheel pip install 2025\". This appears to be related to Python package installation, specifically about girepository (GNOME Introspection Repository) and whether there are manylinux wheels available for pip installation in 2025.\n\nLet me perform this search.\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"PyGObject>=3.51.0 depends on libgirepository 2.0 #3143 - GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/beeware/toga/issues/3143\"},{\"title\":\"pip - I want to install package gi in the python, but it shows error and\",\"url\":\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/74026979/i-want-to-install-package-gi-in-the-python-but-it-shows-error-and-warning\"},{\"title\":\"PyGObject - PyPI\",\"url\":\"https://pypi.org/project/PyGObject/\"},{\"title\":\"Changelog for PyInstaller — PyInstaller 6.12.0 documentation\",\"url\":\"https://pyinstaller.org/en/v6.12.0/CHANGES.html\"},{\"title\":\"[PDF] Matplotlib.pdf\",\"url\":\"https://matplotlib.org/stable/Matplotlib.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Error for create project hello world - briefcase dev - Ubuntu 24.10\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/issues/2235\"},{\"title\":\"Changes.20251015.txt - FTP Server of the GWDG\",\"url\":\"https://ftp5.gwdg.de/pub/linux/suse/opensuse/ports/aarch64/tumbleweed/iso/Changes.20251015.txt\"},{\"title\":\"Linux Magazine - February 2026 - En-1 - Scribd\",\"url\":\"https://www.scribd.com/document/1009535637/Linux-Magazine-February-2026-En-1\"},{\"title\":\"The Wireless Cookbook: Build Real Projects and Master Wi-Fi\",\"url\":\"https://dokumen.pub/the-wireless-cookbook-build-real-projects-and-master-wi-fi-bluetooth-and-lora-early-access-edition.html\"},{\"title\":\"openSUSE Factory\",\"url\":\"https://lists.opensuse.org/archives/list/factory@lists.opensuse.org/latest?count=200&page=1\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here is the current situation regarding `girepository-2.0` and manylinux wheels for pip installation in 2025:\n\n## Key Findings:\n\n### PyGObject and libgirepository-2.0 Dependency\n- **PyGObject >= 3.51.0** now depends on **libgirepository-2.0** (as of February 2025)\n- This dependency change has caused some concerns because it appears to deprecate support for non-EOL platforms like **Ubuntu 22.04**\n- This is a significant change for developers trying to install PyGObject via pip on various Linux distributions\n\n### Manylinux Wheel Status\n- There is **limited information** about official manylinux wheels specifically for `girepository-2.0` being available on PyPI as of late 2025\n- The search results show that manylinux wheel support continues to expand (e.g., ppc64le wheels being added), but specific `girepository-2.0` manylinux wheels are not clearly documented\n\n### Installation Challenges\n- Installing `gi` (PyGObject) via pip often shows errors and warnings because it typically requires system-level GObject introspection libraries\n- Traditional installation usually requires:\n  - System packages (like `libgirepository-1.0-dev`, `gir1.2-glib-2.0`, etc.)\n  - Building from source with proper dependencies\n\n### Recommendations\n1. **Check PyPI directly** for the latest PyGObject wheel availability: https://pypi.org/project/PyGObject/\n2. **For Ubuntu/Debian**: You may need to install system dependencies first:\n   ```bash\n   sudo apt-get install libgirepository-2.0-dev gir1.2-glib-2.0\n   pip install PyGObject\n   ```\n3. **For manylinux compatibility**: The transition to girepository-2.0 may require updated manylinux standards or distribution-specific solutions\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about manylinux wheel availability for girepository-2.0 or installation instructions for a particular Linux distribution?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"103cb0b3-2c64-4af6-9698-f7dcc320b7b5","uuid":"455821b2-ebc8-434a-9372-bc58e6902eba","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:39:59.057Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"girepository-2.0 manylinux wheel pip install 2025","results":["The user wants me to search for information about \"girepository-2.0 manylinux wheel pip install 2025\". This appears to be related to Python package installation, specifically about girepository (GNOME Introspection Repository) and whether there are manylinux wheels available for pip installation in 2025.\n\nLet me perform this search.",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_c6bf3c60c7a64c1385a03bc5","content":[{"title":"PyGObject>=3.51.0 depends on libgirepository 2.0 #3143 - GitHub","url":"https://github.com/beeware/toga/issues/3143"},{"title":"pip - I want to install package gi in the python, but it shows error and","url":"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/74026979/i-want-to-install-package-gi-in-the-python-but-it-shows-error-and-warning"},{"title":"PyGObject - PyPI","url":"https://pypi.org/project/PyGObject/"},{"title":"Changelog for PyInstaller — PyInstaller 6.12.0 documentation","url":"https://pyinstaller.org/en/v6.12.0/CHANGES.html"},{"title":"[PDF] Matplotlib.pdf","url":"https://matplotlib.org/stable/Matplotlib.pdf"},{"title":"Error for create project hello world - briefcase dev - Ubuntu 24.10","url":"https://github.com/beeware/briefcase/issues/2235"},{"title":"Changes.20251015.txt - FTP Server of the GWDG","url":"https://ftp5.gwdg.de/pub/linux/suse/opensuse/ports/aarch64/tumbleweed/iso/Changes.20251015.txt"},{"title":"Linux Magazine - February 2026 - En-1 - Scribd","url":"https://www.scribd.com/document/1009535637/Linux-Magazine-February-2026-En-1"},{"title":"The Wireless Cookbook: Build Real Projects and Master Wi-Fi","url":"https://dokumen.pub/the-wireless-cookbook-build-real-projects-and-master-wi-fi-bluetooth-and-lora-early-access-editio